cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the optimization of the path from crowdsourcers to end-users, which involves network architecture and protocols. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with live streaming of video content, which falls under the category of multimedia. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a framework for cost-effective cloud service for crowdsourced live streaming, which involves distributed computing. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents an optimal solution for service migration among cloud instances, which involves algorithms and data structures. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the dynamics of video sources and the globalized request demands, which can be modeled as a control system.
